  "root_text": {
    "iti89:0.1": "Itivuttaka 89 ",
    "iti89:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti89:0.3": "Catutthavagga ",
    "iti89:0.4": "Devadattasutta ",
    "iti89:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti89:2.1": "“Tīhi, bhikkhave, asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho. ",
    "iti89:2.2": "Katamehi tīhi? ",
    "iti89:2.3": "Pāpicchatāya, bhikkhave, abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho. ",
    "iti89:2.4": "Pāpamittatāya, bhikkhave, abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho. ",
    "iti89:2.5": "Sati kho pana uttarikaraṇīye oramattakena visesādhigamena antarā vosānaṁ āpādi. ",
    "iti89:2.6": "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho”ti. ",
    "iti89:2.7": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti89:2.8": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti89:3.1": "“Mā jātu koci lokasmiṁ, ",
    "iti89:3.2": "pāpiccho udapajjatha; ",
    "iti89:3.3": "Tadamināpi jānātha, ",
    "iti89:3.4": "pāpicchānaṁ yathā gati. ",
    "iti89:4.1": "Paṇḍitoti samaññāto, ",
    "iti89:4.2": "bhāvitattoti sammato; ",
    "iti89:4.3": "Jalaṁva yasasā aṭṭhā, ",
    "iti89:4.4": "devadattoti vissuto. ",
    "iti89:5.1": "So samānamanuciṇṇo, ",
    "iti89:5.2": "āsajja naṁ tathāgataṁ; ",
    "iti89:5.3": "Avīcinirayaṁ patto, ",
    "iti89:5.4": "catudvāraṁ bhayānakaṁ. ",
    "iti89:6.1": "Aduṭṭhassa hi yo dubbhe, ",
    "iti89:6.2": "pāpakammaṁ akubbato; ",
    "iti89:6.3": "Tameva pāpaṁ phusati, ",
    "iti89:6.4": "duṭṭhacittaṁ anādaraṁ. ",
    "iti89:7.1": "Samuddaṁ visakumbhena, ",
    "iti89:7.2": "yo maññeyya padūsituṁ; ",
    "iti89:7.3": "Na so tena padūseyya, ",
    "iti89:7.4": "bhesmā hi udadhi mahā. ",
    "iti89:8.1": "Evamevaṁ tathāgataṁ, ",
    "iti89:8.2": "yo vādena vihiṁsati; ",
    "iti89:8.3": "Sammaggataṁ santacittaṁ, ",
    "iti89:8.4": "vādo tamhi na rūhati. ",
    "iti89:9.1": "Tādisaṁ mittaṁ kubbetha, ",
    "iti89:9.2": "tañca seveyya paṇḍito; ",
    "iti89:9.3": "Yassa maggānugo bhikkhu, ",
    "iti89:9.4": "khayaṁ dukkhassa pāpuṇe”ti. ",
    "iti89:10.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti89:10.2": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "iti89:10.3": "Catuttho vaggo. ",
    "iti89:11.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "iti89:11.1": "Vitakkāsakkārasadda, ",
    "iti89:11.2": "cavanaloke asubhaṁ; ",
    "iti89:11.3": "Dhammaandhakāramalaṁ, ",
    "iti89:11.4": "devadattena te dasāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti89:0.1": "So It Was Said 89 ",
    "iti89:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti89:0.3": "Chapter Four ",
    "iti89:0.4": "About Devadatta ",
    "iti89:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti89:2.1": "“Mendicants, overcome and overwhelmed by three things that oppose the true teaching, Devadatta is going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable. ",
    "iti89:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti89:2.3": "Corrupt wishes … ",
    "iti89:2.4": "Bad friendship … ",
    "iti89:2.5": "When there is still more to be done, stopping half-way after achieving some trifling distinction. ",
    "iti89:2.6": "Overcome and overwhelmed by these three things that oppose the true teaching, Devadatta is going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable.” ",
    "iti89:2.7": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti89:2.8": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti89:3.1": "“Let none of wicked desire ",
    "iti89:3.2": "ever be reborn into this world. ",
    "iti89:3.3": "And by this too you should know ",
    "iti89:3.4": "the place where those of corrupt wishes go. ",
    "iti89:4.1": "He once was considered astute, ",
    "iti89:4.2": "deemed to be evolved, ",
    "iti89:4.3": "his glory stood forth like a flame, ",
    "iti89:4.4": "the renowned Devadatta. ",
    "iti89:5.1": "Seduced by heedlessness, ",
    "iti89:5.2": "he attacked the Realized One. ",
    "iti89:5.3": "He has fallen to Avīci hell, ",
    "iti89:5.4": "four-doored and terrifying. ",
    "iti89:6.1": "When someone betrays the innocent, ",
    "iti89:6.2": "who have done no wrong, ",
    "iti89:6.3": "their bad deeds impact the one ",
    "iti89:6.4": "with corrupt heart, lacking regard for others. ",
    "iti89:7.1": "One might think to pollute ",
    "iti89:7.2": "the ocean with a pot of poison, ",
    "iti89:7.3": "but it wouldn’t work, ",
    "iti89:7.4": "for the sea is terribly large. ",
    "iti89:8.1": "So too when someone attacks ",
    "iti89:8.2": "with words the Realized One—",
    "iti89:8.3": "rightly comported, of peaceful mind—",
    "iti89:8.4": "the words don’t take. ",
    "iti89:9.1": "The astute would befriend one like this, ",
    "iti89:9.2": "and follow them around. ",
    "iti89:9.3": "A mendicant who walks the path ",
    "iti89:9.4": "attains the ending of suffering.” ",
    "iti89:10.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti89:2.5": "uttarikaraṇīye → uttariṁ karaṇīye (sya-all) | visesādhigamena → visesādhigamena ca (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "iti89:4.4": "vissuto → me sutaṁ (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "iti89:5.1": "samānamanuciṇṇo → pamāṇamanuciṇṇo (bj, csp1ed); pamādamanuciṇṇo (si, sya-all) ",
    "iti89:6.3": "phusati → phusseti (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "iti89:8.1": "Evamevaṁ → evameva (bj); evametaṁ (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "iti89:8.3": "Sammaggataṁ → samaggataṁ (bj, mr) "
  },
